---
import SiteLayout from '../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "The Ultimate Seasonal Home Maintenance Checklist",
    "description": "A comprehensive home maintenance checklist by season. Includes essential tasks for spring, summer, fall, and winter to keep your house in top condition.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "I Just Want To"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often should I clean my gutters?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Gutters should be cleaned at least twice a year—once in the spring and once in the fall after the leaves have dropped. If you have many trees near your roof, you may need to clean them more frequently."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I service my HVAC system?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "HVAC systems should be serviced twice a year: schedule an AC checkup in the spring and a furnace or heating system inspection in the fall before the extreme weather hits."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How frequently do smoke detectors need new batteries?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Smoke and carbon monoxide detector batteries should be replaced at least once a year. A good habit is to change them when you adjust your clocks for Daylight Saving Time."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is it worth paying a pro for roof inspections?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, hiring a professional for a roof inspection every 1-2 years is highly recommended. They can spot small leaks, damaged flashing, or missing shingles before they turn into costly structural damage."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the most critical winter maintenance task?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Preventing frozen pipes is the most critical winter task. Ensure exterior faucets are drained, hoses are disconnected, and pipes in unheated areas (like basements or attics) are properly insulated."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

export const meta = {
  title: "Seasonal Home Maintenance Checklist | I Just Want To",
  description: "A comprehensive home maintenance checklist organized by season. 60+ critical tasks to protect your home's value, from HVAC to roof inspections.",
  category: "list",
  published: "2026-03-21",
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="ijustwantto"
  title="Seasonal Home Maintenance Checklist | I Just Want To"
  description="A comprehensive home maintenance checklist organized by season. 60+ critical tasks to protect your home's value, from HVAC to roof inspections."
  canonical="https://ijustwantto.live/home-maintenance-checklist"
  schema={schema}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>The Ultimate Home Maintenance Checklist by Season</h1>
      <p>Keep your home safe, efficient, and valuable with this comprehensive year-round guide.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="content-section">
      <p>Owning a home is a massive investment, and ignoring routine maintenance is a guaranteed way to lose money. A small leak ignored in the spring becomes a mold remediation nightmare in the summer. A clogged gutter in the fall becomes a cracked foundation in the winter.</p>

      <p>To keep you on track, we have organized the ultimate home maintenance checklist by season. Use this guide to plan your weekends, decide when to hire a professional, and ensure you never miss a critical task.</p>

      <div class="print-callout">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Use your browser's print function to print this page—the layout is optimized to be printer-friendly so you can check off tasks as you go!
      </div>

      <h2 id="spring">Spring Maintenance Checklist</h2>
      <p>Spring is the time to assess winter damage and prepare your home for the rainy season and summer heat.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <ul class="task-list">
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect the roof and shingles</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY Inspect, Pro Repair</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look for missing, curled, or damaged shingles from winter storms. Check flashing around chimneys and vents.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean gutters and downspouts</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Remove debris so spring rains can flow freely. Ensure downspouts direct water at least 5 feet away from the foundation.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Schedule HVAC AC servicing</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Have a technician clean coils, check refrigerant levels, and inspect ductwork before the summer heat hits.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check exterior drainage and grading</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Ensure the soil slopes away from your foundation to prevent basement flooding during heavy rains.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect exterior caulking and weatherstripping</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Check the seals around windows and doors. Recaulk any areas where the seal is cracked or missing to prevent water intrusion.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Service the lawn mower and yard equipment</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Change the oil, sharpen blades, and replace spark plugs so your equipment is ready for the growing season.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Test the sump pump</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Pour a bucket of water into the sump pit to ensure the pump turns on and correctly discharges the water.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect wooden decks and fences</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look for signs of rot, loose boards, or popped nails. Plan for power washing and resealing if water no longer beads on the surface.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Wash exterior windows and screens</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 3 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Clean winter grime off windows and repair any tears in screens before installing them.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Examine driveway and walkways</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look for cracks in concrete or asphalt caused by freezing and thawing. Seal cracks to prevent weed growth and further damage.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check smoke and carbon monoxide detectors</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Test the alarms and replace batteries if you didn't do so during Daylight Saving Time.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect plumbing for leaks</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Check under all sinks, around toilets, and near the water heater for signs of moisture or dripping.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean the refrigerator coils</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Vacuum the coils behind or under your fridge to improve efficiency and extend the appliance's life.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check fire extinguishers</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Ensure the pressure gauge is in the green zone and the extinguishers are easily accessible.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Turn on exterior plumbing</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Open the valves for outdoor hose bibs and check for any freeze damage or leaks that occurred over winter.</div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="summer">Summer Maintenance Checklist</h2>
      <p>Summer is perfect for outdoor projects and ensuring your home remains cool and energy-efficient.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <ul class="task-list">
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect foundation and crawlspace</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY Inspect, Pro Repair</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Check for new cracks, signs of moisture, or insect activity around the perimeter and in the crawlspace/basement.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Prune trees and shrubs</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 3 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY or Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Keep branches at least 3 feet away from your home's exterior to prevent damage to the roof or siding and deter pests.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean and repair siding</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 4 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Power wash vinyl or fiber cement siding to remove dirt and mildew. Repair any damaged or loose sections.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check exterior paint</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look for peeling, blistering, or chipping paint. Scraping and touching up spots protects the underlying wood from rot.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean the exhaust fan in the bathroom</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Remove the cover and vacuum dust to ensure the fan effectively removes humidity and prevents mold.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect and clean the dryer vent</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY or Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Lint buildup in the dryer exhaust tube is a major fire hazard. Clean the tube from the back of the dryer to the exterior vent.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check window locks and mechanisms</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Ensure all windows open, close, and lock smoothly. Lubricate tracks if necessary.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Flush the water heater</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Drain a few gallons from the water heater to remove sediment buildup, which improves efficiency and extends the tank's life.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect outdoor play equipment</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Check swings, slides, and playsets for loose bolts, splintering wood, or rust.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Maintain the garage door</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Lubricate the rollers, tracks, and hinges with a garage door-specific spray. Test the auto-reverse safety feature.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check for plumbing leaks under sinks</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">A quick mid-year check ensures no small drips have started under the kitchen or bathroom sinks.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean kitchen range hood filter</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Soak the metal filter in hot soapy water or run it through the dishwasher to remove grease buildup.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect the driveway for weeds</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Remove weeds growing in concrete or asphalt cracks, as their roots can expand and worsen the damage.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check washing machine hoses</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look for bulges, cracks, or leaks in the rubber hoses. Consider replacing them with braided steel hoses to prevent flooding.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Seal the deck or patio</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 4 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">If you power washed in the spring, summer is the perfect dry time to apply a new coat of sealer or stain.</div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="fall">Fall Maintenance Checklist</h2>
      <p>Fall maintenance is all about winterizing your home to protect it from freezing temperatures, snow, and ice.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <ul class="task-list">
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean gutters and downspouts (again)</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY or Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Wait until most leaves have fallen. Clogged gutters in winter lead to devastating ice dams on your roof.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Schedule HVAC heating servicing</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Have your furnace or heat pump inspected and cleaned before you turn it on for the winter to prevent dangerous carbon monoxide leaks.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Winterize exterior plumbing</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Disconnect garden hoses, drain them, and store them. Shut off interior valves to outdoor spigots and leave the exterior spigot open to drain.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect and sweep the chimney</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: Pro</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Hire a chimney sweep to remove highly flammable creosote buildup if you use a wood-burning fireplace.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Seal gaps and cracks</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Walk the exterior and use caulk or expanding foam to seal anywhere cold air or mice could enter your home.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check weatherstripping on doors/windows</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Replace worn weatherstripping to stop drafts and keep your heating bills low.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Test the sump pump</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Test it again to ensure it's ready for melting snow or heavy autumn rains.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Drain and store gas-powered equipment</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Run your lawn mower until it's out of gas or add a fuel stabilizer so the carburetor doesn't gum up over winter.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Service the snowblower</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Change the oil, check the spark plug, and test-start the snowblower before the first blizzard hits.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check attic insulation and ventilation</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Ensure insulation is adequate and hasn't compressed. Verify that soffit vents are not blocked to prevent ice dams.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Replace HVAC air filters</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Change out the filters to ensure maximum airflow and efficiency as heating season begins.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Test smoke and CO detectors</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Since windows will be closed and heating appliances running, functional CO detectors are absolutely vital.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect the roof before winter</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY Inspect, Pro Repair</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Do a visual inspection from the ground to ensure no summer storms damaged shingles before the snow flies.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Rake and compost leaves</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 3 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Don't let a thick mat of leaves sit on your lawn over winter, as it can kill the grass and promote mold.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check foundation vents</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">If you have a crawlspace, close the foundation vents for the winter to keep pipes from freezing.</div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2 id="winter">Winter Maintenance Checklist</h2>
      <p>Winter maintenance focuses on monitoring your home for storm damage, managing moisture, and indoor upkeep.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <ul class="task-list">
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Monitor for ice dams</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: Ongoing | Pro Recommendation: DIY Monitor, Pro Repair</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Watch the edge of your roof for thick ridges of ice. If they form, they can force melting snow under your shingles.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check for drafts on cold days</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Walk around windows and doors on a windy day. Feel for drafts and make notes of areas to seal in the spring.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean the garbage disposal</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Run ice cubes and lemon peels through the disposal to sharpen blades and remove odors.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Deep clean the house</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 4 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Since you're stuck inside, take time to dust ceiling fans, clean baseboards, and vacuum behind heavy furniture.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check basement for moisture</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">During winter thaws, check the basement walls and floor for any signs of water intrusion or dampness.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Inspect the bathroom caulk</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Look at the caulking around tubs and showers. If it's peeling or moldy, strip it and apply a fresh bead to prevent water damage.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Clean showerheads and faucet aerators</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Unscrew aerators and soak them in vinegar to remove mineral deposits and improve water pressure.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Test GFCI outlets</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Press the "test" button on outlets in the kitchen, bathrooms, and exterior to ensure the safety breaker works.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Vacuum refrigerator coils</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Another quick vacuuming helps the fridge run efficiently, which is especially important before loading it up for holidays.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check fire extinguishers</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Verify pressure gauges again. Winter means more cooking, candles, and heating appliances—all fire risks.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Organize tools and supplies</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 2 hours | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Take inventory of your tools, screws, and maintenance supplies so you are ready for spring projects.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Replace HVAC air filters</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Critical | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Keep checking and replacing the furnace filter every 1-3 months while the system is running heavily.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Check locks and deadbolts</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 15 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Ensure all exterior doors lock smoothly. Apply graphite powder lubricant to sticky keyholes.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Tighten handles, knobs, and hinges</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Optional | Time: 30 mins | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Walk through the house with a screwdriver and tighten any loose cabinet knobs or door hinges.</div>
          </li>
          <li class="task-item">
            <div class="task-header"><strong>Review home inventory</strong></div>
            <div class="task-meta">Priority: Important | Time: 1 hour | Pro Recommendation: DIY</div>
            <div class="task-desc">Update your home inventory with any major purchases or gifts received over the holidays for insurance purposes.</div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- FAQs -->
    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How often should I clean my gutters?</h3>
          <p>Gutters should be cleaned at least twice a year—once in the spring and once in the fall after the leaves have dropped. If you have many trees near your roof, you may need to clean them more frequently.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>When should I service my HVAC system?</h3>
          <p>HVAC systems should be serviced twice a year: schedule an AC checkup in the spring and a furnace or heating system inspection in the fall before the extreme weather hits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How frequently do smoke detectors need new batteries?</h3>
          <p>Smoke and carbon monoxide detector batteries should be replaced at least once a year. A good habit is to change them when you adjust your clocks for Daylight Saving Time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is it worth paying a pro for roof inspections?</h3>
          <p>Yes, hiring a professional for a roof inspection every 1-2 years is highly recommended. They can spot small leaks, damaged flashing, or missing shingles before they turn into costly structural damage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What is the most critical winter maintenance task?</h3>
